.TH "HTMLDIALOGELEMENT.SHOW" "3JS" "January 26, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLDialogElement.show \- HTMLDialogElement: show() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]show()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLDialogElement\f[R] interface displays the dialog as a
non\-modal dialog.
.PP
A non\-modal dialog is one where users can interact with content
outside/behind the open dialog.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
show()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the dialog is already open and modal (i.e., if the dialog has
already been opened with \f[CR]HTMLDialogElement.showModal()\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic usage
The following example shows a simple button that, when clicked, opens a
\f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] using the \f[CR]show()\f[R] method.
.PP
When the dialog is open, you can still interact with the rest of the
page, including clicking the \f[I]Click me\f[R] button that triggers an
alert.
.PP
You can click the \f[I]Close dialog\f[R] button to close the dialog (via
the \f[CR]close()\f[R] method).
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]dialog\f[R] id=\(dqdialog\(dq>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] type=\(dqbutton\(dq id=\(dqclose\(dq>Close dialog</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]dialog\f[R]>

<\f[B]p\f[R]><\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqopen\(dq>Open dialog</\f[B]button\f[R]></\f[B]p\f[R]>
<\f[B]p\f[R]><\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqalert\(dq>Trigger alert</\f[B]button\f[R]></\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dialog = document.getElementById(\(dqdialog\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] openButton = document.getElementById(\(dqopen\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] closeButton = document.getElementById(\(dqclose\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] alertButton = document.getElementById(\(dqalert\(dq);

\f[I]// Open button opens a modeless dialog\f[R]
openButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  dialog.show();
});

\f[I]// Alert button triggers an alert\f[R]
alertButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  alert(\(dqyou clicked me!\(dq);
});

\f[I]// Close button closes the dialog box\f[R]
closeButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  dialog.close();
});
.EE
.SS Result
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
HTML \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] element
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLDialogElement.showModal()\f[R]
